# Release + publish — agent checklist

> **Trigger:** version bump, `git tag`, npm publish, GitHub Release, `release.yml`, CHANGELOG.

## Non-negotiable order

1. `pnpm verify` green on `developing`
2. PR `developing` → `main` (CI `test` + approval)
3. **Bump version** in **both** publishable packages (same semver)
4. **CHANGELOG** — move `[Unreleased]` → `[X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
5. Commit + merge to `main`
6. **Only then** create and push git tag `vX.Y.Z`
7. Release workflow publishes npm + GitHub Release
8. Sync `developing` from `main`

**NEVER** push a tag before step 3–5. Release CI fails with:

```
Tag version X.Y.Z does not match package.json (core=…, cli=…)
```

## Files that MUST match

| File | Field |
|------|--------|
| `packages/br-validators/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `apps/cli/package.json` | `"version"` |
| Git tag | `v` + same semver (e.g. `v0.11.0-alpha.1`) |

Adapter packages (`@br-validators/zod`, `@br-validators/react-hook-form`) are **not** npm-published yet — do not require tag sync unless added to `release.yml`.

## Pre-tag verification (run before `git tag`)

```bash
VERSION="0.11.0-alpha.1"   # planned release — no v prefix
CORE=$(jq -r .version packages/br-validators/package.json)
CLI=$(jq -r .version apps/cli/package.json)
test "$VERSION" = "$CORE" && test "$CORE" = "$CLI" && echo "OK" || echo "MISMATCH — fix package.json first"
git tag -l "v$VERSION"     # must be empty before new tag
```

## Tag + publish (automated)

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git tag -a v0.11.0-alpha.1 -m "Release v0.11.0-alpha.1"
git push origin v0.11.0-alpha.1
```

Workflow: `.github/workflows/release.yml` — requires secret **`NPM_TOKEN`**. Publishes with dist-tag `alpha` (or `beta`/`rc`/`latest` by version) and updates npm **`latest`** so [npmjs.com](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@br-validators/core) shows the current release.

## Common mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Tag `v0.11.0-alpha.1` but `package.json` still `0.11.0-alpha.0` | Bump both `package.json`, merge `main`, delete bad tag, retag |
| Tag on wrong commit (old code) | Delete remote tag + release; tag `main` HEAD after merge |
| `ERR_PNPM_GIT_UNCLEAN` on local publish | Commit first; CI uses `--no-git-checks` |
| Re-tag same version already on npm | Bump to next patch/prerelease — npm rejects duplicate |
| `core` and `cli` different versions | Set both to identical semver before tag |

## Agent duties on release tasks

1. Bump **both** `package.json` files in the same commit.
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md` for the release scope only.
3. Run pre-tag verification commands; report mismatch before tagging.
4. Do **not** paste or commit `NPM_TOKEN` — GitHub secret only.
5. After release, confirm: `npm view @br-validators/core@alpha version` and GitHub Release URL.

**Docs:** `docs/BRANCHING.md`, `docs/VERSIONING.md` — **Troubleshooting:** `npm-publish-ci.mdc`
